title: Readout of Vice President Mike Pence’s Meeting with the Prime Minister of the Arab Republic of Egypt – The White House
content:
Statements & Releases			

		Foreign Policy	

Issued on:
October 15, 2019
The Vice President met today with Prime Minister of the Arab Republic of Egypt Dr. Mostafa Madbouly at the White House.  The two leaders highlighted the importance of the strategic partnership between the United States and Egypt.  They exchanged views on regional security issues. The Vice President welcomed the Prime Minister’s commitment to advance discussions on several human rights cases of mutual concern, including Americans detained in Egypt.
